f(t-T) \Leftrightarrow e^{-jwT}F(w)
e^{jwT}f(t) \Leftrightarrow F(w-W)
f(t-T)
f(x)
L^1
f
y
g(x):= f(x-y) \,.
\hat{g}(\chi) = \int_{R^d} g(x) e^{2 \pi i x \cdot \chi} dx =  \int_{R^d} f(x-y) e^{2 \pi i x \cdot \chi} dx 
=  \int_{R^d} f(x-y) e^{2 \pi i (x-y) \cdot \chi}e^{2 \pi i y \cdot \chi} dx = e^{2 \pi i y \cdot \chi}\hat{f}(\chi) \,.
